==English==
[[Category:English words with multiple etymologies]]
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'mə:də/

===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[morþor]]'', influenced in Middle English by Old French ''[[murdre]]'' (French ''[[meurtre]]''), itself from Germanic.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|murder|murders}}
#{{countable}} An act of [[deliberate]] [[killing]].
#: ''There have been ten unsolved murders this year alone.''
#{{uncountable}} {{law}} The [[crime]] of [[deliberate]] [[killing]].
#: ''The defendant was charged with murder.''
#{{uncountable}} ''(When used as a predicative noun)'': [[terrible|Terrible]] to [[endure]].
#: ''This headache is murder.''
# {{countable}} The [[collective noun]] for [[crow]]s

